<div class="heading resPageHeading">


























<h1 >Paying Vendors</h1></div>

<div class="content stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="ed9d9f2a-d54a-4d2c-a873-43e60c7d71fb" >

    <p>To initiate payment to a vendor, an invoice must be submitted to Financial Services. Payment will be made within Ryerson’s payment terms as long as:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>an approved purchase requisition (PR) is in place;</li> 
 <li>a purchase order (PO) has been created prior to the delivery of goods or commencement of services;</li> 
 <li>a Ryerson PO number is included on the vendor’s invoice</li> 
</ul> 
<p><strong>Note that payment processing will be delayed if your vendor submits an invoice without a PO number.</strong> For more on the invoice requirement process, visit the <a href="/content/ryerson/financial-services/purchasing-payment/vendor-guidance.html">Vendor Guidance page</a>.</p> 
<p>If you’re paying an independent contractor, please be sure to review the&nbsp;<a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/hr/manager-resources/hiring/independent-contractors/">Human Resources website</a>&nbsp;for guidance on determining independent contractor status. If independent contractor status is met based on the Employment Relationship and Payment Decision Tree,&nbsp;please remember to include the completed <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/content/dam/gcbs/legal-services/AgreementContractorSupplier.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>Professional Services Agreement document<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span></a> with your submission.</p> 
<h2><a id="purchases-under-5000"></a>Purchases less than $5,000</h2> 
<p>You can <strong>now place all orders less than $5,000</strong>, including service-related orders,<strong> directly with vendors without the need for a purchase order</strong>. For service-related purchases, please instruct vendors to complete the new <a href="/content/dam/financial-services/purchasing-payment/docs/service-agreement-under-5000-form.pdf"><span class="sr-only">PDF file</span>Service Agreement (Under $5,000)<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-file-pdf-o"></span></a> contract prior to commencing the work.</p> 
<h2><a id="forms-payment"></a>Forms of payment</h2> 
<p>By default, payments in Canadian and U.S. currency are made by cheque while payments in all other currencies are made by wire transfer.</p> 
<h2>Additional forms of payment</h2> 
<p>There are two additional methods for vendor payments:</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#ed9d9f2a-d54a-4d2c-a873-43e60c7d71fb");});</script></div>

				

				
