<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="45e02158-666d-4517-ade5-40685360fe83" >

    <h2><a name="alternative"></a>Alternative payment methods</h2> 
<p>If credit cards are not accepted or if an invoice is not available from your vendor, we offer payment options for both scenarios:</p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#45e02158-666d-4517-ade5-40685360fe83");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resAccordion section">
























 


<div class="row">
    <div class="col-xs-12">
        <div class="panel-group accordion background-hidden" id="65369496-521c-459b-ada7-342930418930" role="tablist" aria-multiselectable="true">
			
				<div class="resAccordionControl" role="group" aria-label="Accordion Actions">
					<button class="resAccordionOpenAll">Open All</button> <button class="resAccordionCloseAll">Close All</button>
				</div>
				<script type="text/javascript">$(document).ready(function(){ initResAccordionControl("65369496-521c-459b-ada7-342930418930", false); });</script>
			
            
            <div class="panel panel-default">
                <!-- Accordion Heading -->
                <div class="panel-heading container-clipboard">
                    <h3 class="panel-title">
                        <a id="accordion-1534946318479-self-service-invoice--ssi-" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1534946318479-self-service-invoice--ssi-" aria-controls="accordion-content-1534946318479-self-service-invoice--ssi-" aria-expanded="false">
                            Self-service invoice (SSI)
                        </a>
                    </h3>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1534946318479-self-service-invoice--ssi-" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1534946318479-self-service-invoice--ssi-">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1534946318479 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="af79e986-7c36-46cc-b028-7d19557cd01c" >

    <p>The Self-Service Invoice (SSI) entry process in the <a href="https://mv.rufis.ryerson.ca/markview/MVT_MV_Home.Home">Invoice Approval System</a> is appropriate for processing payments less than $5,000 CAD when the Ryerson Purchasing Card (P-Card) is not accepted by the vendor, although some <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/financial-services/purchasing-payment/paying-vendors/#p-card-ssi-exceptions">exceptions</a> apply.</p> 
<p>Note this option requires an SSI training session. Find available dates on the HR <a href="https://hr.apps.ccs.ryerson.ca/lec">Learning Events Calendar</a>.</p> 
<p>To use the SSI process:</p> 
<ol> 
 <li>Place an order directly with your vendor and have the vendor’s invoice sent to your department.</li> 
 <li>If your vendor is new to Ryerson, please have them complete a <a href="https://ryersonfs.wufoo.com/forms/m44wsgc167ubyb/">Vendor Application Form<span aria-hidden="true" class="autoIconLink fa fa-external-link"></span><span class="sr-only">, external link</span></a>. Details from this form will be used to set up the vendor in Ryerson’s financial systems.</li> 
 <li>Once goods are received, enter the vendor’s invoice using the self-service invoice (SSI) entry process in the <a href="https://mv.rufis.ryerson.ca/markview/MVT_MV_Home.Home">Invoice Approval System (MarkView)</a>. Be sure to upload a copy of the vendor’s invoice with your SSI entry prior to submitting for approval.</li> 
</ol> 
<p>Invoices entered into SSI will be forwarded for approval and payment once approved. Note the following when using the SSI option:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>purchase requisitions are not required</li> 
 <li>the vendor must send the invoice directly to the requesting department</li> 
 <li>requests for payment must have the supplier invoice electronically attached prior to being sent to the approver</li> 
</ul> 
<h3>Two tips when starting the SSI entry process</h3> 
<p>If SSI entries are new to you, here are two tips that can help you navigate the process:</p> 
<ol> 
 <li>Most purchases are subject to a 13 per cent HST payment. When submitting your SSI entry, be sure to select a tax code that reflects the applicable taxes listed on the vendor’s invoice. If you need help identifying the correct tax code, please contact <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/financial-services/contact/purchasing-payment/#payment-services">Payment Services</a>.</li> 
 <li>Ryerson’s payment terms are net 30 days from the invoice date. If you need to check the status of an invoice payment or cancel an entry you submitted, please contact <a href="https://www.ryerson.ca/financial-services/contact/purchasing-payment/#payment-services">Payment Services</a>.</li> 
</ol>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#af79e986-7c36-46cc-b028-7d19557cd01c");});</script></div>

				</div>

                    </div>
